node.text:
Last February (pre covid lol) I decided to knock something off my bucket list and I GOT MY MOTORCYCLE LICENSE!! I took a 2 day training course with Honda and had sooo much fun. The instructors made me feel so safe and relaxed so I feel like I picked things up with a lot more confidence. I passed my test first try and got my bike right after! (isn’t she cute 💛) #Ad Thank you Honda for partnering with me to check this off the bucket list- dirt bike next?
#BetterOnAHonda #HondaGrom #gromance #HondaPartner

node.text:
most mornings i wake up more exhausted than i was falling asleep. my dreams are fucking heavy and filled with so many messages all the time. they have been alllll my life- my sister and mom have it too! some bloodline shit idk. i often find myself wishing i was less in touch and just coasted through life without any weight/connection to the collective energy. energetic ties to past situations and people can be so draining and literally take over my days/weeks sometimes. i know i’m not alone so i decided to share this with y’all. i’m not seeking pity and i don’t have a solution so that’s not where this is going, but i’m here for you to vent. 
how do you deal with not drowning in that past energy?
